title: KELVIN-CLINIC

creator: MachineMedicine
descriptionHtml: We use Deep Learning computer vision models to track motor dysfunction in patients with neurological conditions.
descriptionShort: Application to record and assess motor dysfunctions.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml: Real-time quality control feedback has been added to video capture. Now when recording a video, the app will inform you if any of the patient’s body is out of frame, and whether the patient is too far or too close from the camera, and for the speech item an audio level will indicate if the patient is talking too quietly or loudly. Following this feedback will ensure you record good quality videos. This feedback can be turned on or off in the settings menu.

title: KELVIN-CLINIC

creator: MachineMedicine
descriptionHtml:
KELVIN-CLINIC enables any operator to video-record motor assessments, using a smartphone or tablet.

Clinicians can seamlessly record video and clinical ratings through the app while conducting motor assessments for movement disorders, with real-time quality control feedback, ensuring the highest quality data is obtained.

Data captured using this app will be uploaded to KELVIN-CLOUD, a web application, that allows fast, reliable, and secure data management for both clinical trials and clinical care. KELVIN-CLOUD also offers state-of-the-art computer vision tools, providing objective biomarkers for clinical research.
descriptionShort: Digitised motor assessment for capturing videos & ratings of movement disorders

appDetails.recentChangesHtml: You can now assess essential tremor using a new assessment form. This can be accessed by clicking on the “New assessment” menu, then selecting “TETRAS”. Any assessments you record will be uploaded and viewable within your account on the KELVIN-CLOUD Web app.

The allowed length of each video has been set to 5 minutes. After recording for 5 minutes the video will automatically stop, in order to prevent issues during long-video uploads.
